<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="68" type="mainText">H. purpurea, nitens, violaceo variegata; metathorace crasse punctatissimo; abdominis margine apicali arcuato, integerrimo; alis subhyalinis.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="68" type="mainText">Length 33/4f lines. Dark blue, with tints of bright purple and green; the head, pro-, and mesothorax finely punctured, the prothorax with large coarse punctures at the sides; the metathorax with large deep fossulets at the sides; wings light brown, with their base hyaline. Abdomen delicately punctured, smooth and shining; the body brilliant green beneath.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="68" type="mainText">Hab. Makassar.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
